===Etymology===
Via Middle English and Old French, ultimately from Latin [[boia]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-boy.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔɪ|-ɔɪ]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#<!--DefA--> A [[young]] [[male]] person, usually a [[child]] or [[teenager]].
#<!--DefB--> (''offensive'') A male [[African-American]] of any age.
#<!--DefC--> A male servant. (Compare French [[garçon]])
#<!--DefD--> (''colloquial, always used as ''the boys) Male friends.
#: ''I’m going out with the '''boys'''.''
#<!--DefE--> (''regional'') A male of any age, used when calling attention to the person.
#: ''Whatever else you say about him, the '''boy''' can play.''
#<!--DefF--> An [[adult]] male, particularly when used by straight women or gay men to refer to someone considered attractive.
#: ''That bar has lots of cute '''boys'''!''

